  "prompt": "How likely is it you will get in trouble for downloading movies via torrent sites in the USA in 2016?",
  "response": "In 2016, the risk of legal consequences for downloading copyrighted movies via torrent sites varied. While many people did download content, copyright holders and internet service providers (ISPs) were actively monitoring and sending warning notices. Potential risks included:\n\n1. Copyright infringement notices from ISP\n2. Potential lawsuits from movie studios\n3. Possible monetary settlements\n4. Temporary internet service interruptions\n\nThe actual likelihood of serious legal consequences depended on factors like:\n- Volume of downloads\n- Specific content downloaded\n- Your internet service provider's policies\n- Whether you were sharing/seeding files\n\nWhile many people downloaded without direct consequences, there was still a meaningful legal risk. Using a VPN could reduce potential tracking.",
